01:02.320 --> 01:04.638
When I was a kid,
my brother and I used to

01:04.640 --> 01:09.031
pretend we were heroes with swords.

01:09.160 --> 01:12.743
We were the only ones
who could save the day.

01:13.760 --> 01:16.945
But perhaps we set
the bar a little bit high.

01:17.440 --> 01:20.466
Maybe we're just regular people.

01:21.200 --> 01:23.519
The ones who get saved.

01:53.880 --> 01:55.791
Dad?

02:00.040 --> 02:01.985
What's your password?

02:03.200 --> 02:04.559
What?

02:04.560 --> 02:10.509
I said, what's your password?

02:16.120 --> 02:17.399
Dad!

02:17.400 --> 02:19.399
I have no fucking idea!

02:19.400 --> 02:20.719
Swear jar.

02:20.720 --> 02:22.039
Fuck the swear jar.

02:22.040 --> 02:24.319
- Aidan.
- I'm sorry, but fuck the swear jar.

02:24.320 --> 02:27.239
That word means sex. You're gonna
have sex with the swear jar?

02:27.240 --> 02:29.039
Okay, Tucker, that's enough, honey.

02:29.040 --> 02:31.319
The code's 1234. What are you doing?

02:31.320 --> 02:33.239
The swear jar is full. Look at it.

02:33.240 --> 02:34.879
The swear jar is all the money

02:34.880 --> 02:36.519
we have to send you to college,

02:36.520 --> 02:38.670
so you should be happy I curse.

02:38.720 --> 02:40.267
I heard you, Dad.

02:40.480 --> 02:43.239
Rabbi Perlman says that cursing
is for the simple-minded.

02:43.240 --> 02:45.239
Well, Rabbi Perlman's
breath is so bad,

02:45.240 --> 02:48.599
it makes God question why he even
bothered creating the universe.

02:48.600 --> 02:50.159
Rabbi Perlman's
praying and God's like,

02:50.160 --> 02:52.679
"Please stop, Perlman.
You're welcome.

02:52.680 --> 02:54.386
"You're welcome!"

02:54.760 --> 02:57.159
Well, if you can curse, then we all
can curse. Is that what you want?

02:57.160 --> 02:59.503
- Fine.
- No!

02:59.760 --> 03:01.944
Grace is not gonna curse.

03:03.440 --> 03:04.599
Fuckhead.

03:04.600 --> 03:05.639
Wow!

03:05.640 --> 03:06.919
- Gracie!
- Whoa!

03:06.920 --> 03:08.359
Mom, Dad said that the other day

03:08.360 --> 03:09.759
when someone stole his parking spot.

03:09.760 --> 03:11.719
I did say that, babe,
but he was a fuckhead.

03:11.720 --> 03:14.399
He was in a yellow Hummer.
Who drives a yellow Hummer?

03:14.400 --> 03:16.239
What, is he going to war on the sun?

03:16.240 --> 03:18.439
Dad, we need this car.

03:18.440 --> 03:20.599
We are not getting an Aston Martin.

03:20.600 --> 03:23.799
But for the next minute only,
you can curse.

03:23.800 --> 03:24.959
Then, hairy balls.

03:26.880 --> 03:29.462
Okay. Come on, guys.

03:32.480 --> 03:34.789
Up, up, up. Seat belts.

03:35.120 --> 03:37.719
Tucker! Yarmulke. Tzitzit.

03:37.720 --> 03:39.599
Oh, come on. What is
wrong with you, man?

03:39.600 --> 03:40.679
Get it together.

03:40.680 --> 03:41.959
I was thinking about
that Aston Martin.

03:41.960 --> 03:43.239
Stop thinking about that car.

03:43.240 --> 03:45.399
It's time to start thinking
about the plight of the Jews.

03:45.400 --> 03:46.879
- What does "plight" mean?
- I have no idea.

03:46.880 --> 03:48.799
Ask the rabbis. That's what
we're paying them for.

03:48.800 --> 03:50.479
Aidan, you have to talk
to your father today.

03:50.480 --> 03:52.919
He still hasn't paid
this semester's tuition.

03:52.920 --> 03:55.079
I hate talking to him about money.
When was it due?

03:55.080 --> 03:56.439
Months ago.

03:56.440 --> 03:58.439
Okay, and they're threatening
to kick the kids out of school

03:58.440 --> 03:59.839
if they don't get a check
by the end of this week.

03:59.840 --> 04:01.399
Maybe it's time we put
them in public school.

04:01.400 --> 04:02.479
- No!
- Yay!

04:02.480 --> 04:04.679
Oh, no, no, no, we're not
putting them in the public school.

04:04.680 --> 04:06.944
I'll talk to him today, okay?

04:07.320 --> 04:08.959
Avoid the rabbis if you see them.

04:08.960 --> 04:10.359
I always do!

04:10.360 --> 04:11.919
- Bye, Mom!
- Bye, baby.

04:11.920 --> 04:13.660
Bye!

04:17.839 --> 04:19.421
Bye, sweetie.

04:29.600 --> 04:31.679
You need help gearing
up back there, Yentl?

04:31.680 --> 04:33.359
Don't call me Yentl.

04:33.360 --> 04:35.759
You can call me Yentl.
I love that movie.

04:35.760 --> 04:37.386
I know. I know.

04:37.640 --> 04:40.479
The boys get to do all the
cool things to honor HaShem,

04:40.480 --> 04:44.039
and I won't get to do anything
remotely cool until I buy my sheitel.

04:44.040 --> 04:45.759
Sheitel? What's that again?

04:45.760 --> 04:47.559
It's a modesty wig.

04:47.560 --> 04:50.359
So, when I get married,
I'll shave my head

04:50.360 --> 04:52.639
and wear a wig for
the rest of my life.

04:52.640 --> 04:54.559
That way only my husband
will find me pretty.

04:54.560 --> 04:57.639
No offense, but that's the weirdest
tradition I've ever heard of.

04:57.640 --> 05:00.039
And it wouldn't even work on
you because you're so pretty

05:00.040 --> 05:02.799
that you'd look even
prettier with a shaved head.

05:02.800 --> 05:05.428
So, it would defeat
the whole purpose.

05:09.800 --> 05:11.904
- Bye, Dad.
- Bye.

05:11.920 --> 05:13.751
Hurry, hurry, hurry.

05:14.200 --> 05:15.906
Hey, guys.

05:16.040 --> 05:19.783
Tucker. Come here. Drill.

05:20.080 --> 05:21.911
I knew it.

05:22.080 --> 05:24.628
I told you. Drill stays at home.

05:25.240 --> 05:27.742
Thank you.

05:28.240 --> 05:29.359
Now go be Jewish.

05:29.360 --> 05:31.359
Why? It's so boring.

05:31.360 --> 05:33.399
I have no idea. Ask the rabbis.

05:33.400 --> 05:35.959
Shalom.

05:37.160 --> 05:38.900
I got it right here.

05:38.920 --> 05:40.239
Oh, come on.

05:40.240 --> 05:42.439
Sorry, just give me a second!

05:58.400 --> 05:59.559
Shalom, Mr. Bloom.

05:59.560 --> 06:02.062
Hey, Rabbi Rosenberg.

06:02.120 --> 06:03.919
Mr. Bloom, Rabbi Twersky

06:03.920 --> 06:05.919
would like to see you in his
office if you have a moment.

06:05.920 --> 06:07.359
Oh, you know, today I can't.

06:07.360 --> 06:08.759
Today, believe it or not,

06:08.760 --> 06:10.759
a moment is something
I just don't have.

06:10.760 --> 06:12.119
I'm gonna have to take a rain check.

06:12.120 --> 06:14.199
Speaking of rain, as you know,

06:14.200 --> 06:17.119
every year to celebrate the
holiday of Tu Bishevat,

06:17.120 --> 06:18.759
we ask the children to donate money

06:18.760 --> 06:20.599
to have a tree planted in Israel.

06:20.600 --> 06:22.639
Yeah, I heard about that, Rabbi.

06:22.640 --> 06:24.679
But when you think
about it, how many trees

06:24.680 --> 06:26.639
do they really need over there?

06:26.640 --> 06:28.999
I feel like Israel is
pretty good on trees.

06:29.000 --> 06:30.479
Which is why, Mr. Bloom,

06:30.480 --> 06:33.950
we encourage the children to plant
a seedling in their own backyard.

06:34.560 --> 06:37.062
You never picked up
your seedling, Mr. Bloom.

06:37.160 --> 06:41.799
Oh, no, no, I'm fine.
Oh, there it is. Okay. Thank you.

06:41.800 --> 06:43.984
Just try not to smoke it.

06:44.720 --> 06:46.221
Clever.

06:46.640 --> 06:47.759
Baruch Hashem.

06:47.760 --> 06:52.151
Yes, bless God. Bless everybody.

06:53.960 --> 06:58.988
I ask you, sir. How many
bangs did Jesus hear?

06:59.000 --> 07:01.799
This entire case is
dependent on your testimony

07:01.800 --> 07:05.509
that on the night of January 7th...

07:09.840 --> 07:14.265
This shit is horrible.
In college, I did Othello.

07:14.400 --> 07:15.679
We all did.

07:15.680 --> 07:17.341
Yup.

07:22.040 --> 07:24.839
Aidan, Paul.

07:24.840 --> 07:27.799
Can I just speak to you both
here for a quick second?

07:27.800 --> 07:31.031
Yeah, sure. Hey, Terry.

07:31.880 --> 07:34.719
Uh... Didn't your agents call you?

07:34.720 --> 07:36.959
We've decided to go
African-American with the role.

07:36.960 --> 07:39.399
Oh. You've got to be kidding me, man.

07:39.400 --> 07:41.479
I've been memorizing this all week.

07:41.480 --> 07:44.551
Does he have to be
a dark black person?

07:45.280 --> 07:47.908
What if he were light-skinned?

07:48.000 --> 07:49.119
Uh...

07:49.120 --> 07:50.679
I'm sorry, guys.

07:50.680 --> 07:52.959
Whoa, whoa, whoa! What about Ortega?

07:52.960 --> 07:55.239
Ortega, there's a guy on
the witness stand, Ortega.

07:55.240 --> 07:57.230
He's an older Hispanic man.

07:59.080 --> 08:00.581
Hola, seÃ±or.

08:01.360 --> 08:05.945
I am on the witness stand
and I only heard one bang.

08:06.440 --> 08:07.941
Uno bang.

08:08.560 --> 08:10.679
There was only one uno bang.

08:10.680 --> 08:13.519
Not three. Uno.

08:13.520 --> 08:15.399
Aidan, please tell me you're not

08:15.400 --> 08:17.279
trying to be an older Hispanic man.

08:17.280 --> 08:18.879
I'm just trying to show
you my range, man.

08:18.880 --> 08:20.519
I really, really need a part.

08:20.520 --> 08:23.227
I'm sorry, guys, all right?

08:24.840 --> 08:28.479
If it's any consolation,
I thought you were Hispanic.

08:28.480 --> 08:30.505
- Gracias.
- De nada.

08:38.799 --> 08:41.780
Fuck!

08:42.480 --> 08:44.519
Oh, yeah, do me like that.

08:44.520 --> 08:47.399
Come on, harder, harder! Oh, yeah.

08:47.400 --> 08:48.947
Catch you at a bad time?

08:49.040 --> 08:51.439
Dad, what the hell?

08:51.440 --> 08:53.465
Trouble in the bedroom, Aidan?

08:54.280 --> 08:57.639
Men have man needs.
Those man needs need to be met.

08:57.640 --> 09:00.079
Well, Sarah doesn't really care
about my man needs right now, Dad.

09:00.080 --> 09:01.199
We have a lot going on.

09:01.200 --> 09:04.159
So, you're taking things into
your own hands, so to speak.

09:04.160 --> 09:07.599
Hilarious. Why haven't you
paid the yeshiva tuition, Dad?

09:07.600 --> 09:10.479
I have aggro rabbis
stalking me in crosswalks.

09:10.480 --> 09:12.079
It's like an Orthodox zombie movie.

09:12.080 --> 09:14.799
We need to talk. But can you
please clean yourself up first?

09:14.800 --> 09:16.599
I can't talk to you with
your pants at your ankles.

09:16.600 --> 09:18.261
Fine.

09:23.800 --> 09:26.302
Kugel, no. Kugel!

09:27.160 --> 09:28.359
Sorry.

09:28.360 --> 09:29.719
I know you can't stand the dog.

09:29.720 --> 09:31.239
He's usually so well trained.

09:31.240 --> 09:34.239
If you trained that dog to
piss everywhere but the lawn,

09:34.240 --> 09:36.559
then you did an incredible job.

09:36.560 --> 09:38.425
Pool looks good.

09:38.520 --> 09:41.466
What are you growing,
typhoid or hepatitis?

09:42.320 --> 09:45.266
What's going on with the fence?

09:45.640 --> 09:48.599
You have a nice little slice
of Mumbai back here, Aidan.

09:48.600 --> 09:50.839
The yard has been this
way since we moved in.

09:50.840 --> 09:52.999
Are you gonna comment on
it every time you see it?

09:53.000 --> 09:54.359
I haven't gotten a decent check

09:54.360 --> 09:55.719
since I did that dandruff commercial.

09:55.720 --> 09:58.826
Ironically, you still have dandruff.

10:00.520 --> 10:03.839
What is going on with
the tuition checks, Dad?

10:03.840 --> 10:05.839
We had a deal.
You said you'd cover it

10:05.840 --> 10:08.079
as long as you got to pick the school.

10:08.080 --> 10:09.359
And you did.

10:09.360 --> 10:11.759
You have your indoctrinated,

10:11.760 --> 10:13.439
little religious grandchildren.

10:13.440 --> 10:15.679
You cannot make me hound
you for these checks.

10:15.680 --> 10:17.944
The cancer's back, Aidan.

10:22.360 --> 10:25.067
I didn't want to worry
you till I knew for sure.

10:25.280 --> 10:27.828
- But now you do.
- Now I do.

10:27.960 --> 10:29.586
And it's pretty bad.

10:30.400 --> 10:32.399
How bad is "pretty bad"?

10:32.400 --> 10:35.439
It's metastasized
from my lungs, spreading.

10:35.440 --> 10:36.959
Oh, my God.

10:36.960 --> 10:39.622
Found this place out in Malibu.

10:39.880 --> 10:41.719
Treats your own stem
cells and then injects

10:41.720 --> 10:43.839
them right back into you.
Good as new.

10:43.840 --> 10:46.229
But I'm going to have
to pay out of pocket.

10:49.160 --> 10:50.399
So...

10:50.400 --> 10:53.631
So, I can't afford the
school anymore, Aidan.

10:53.680 --> 10:56.919
I'm down to my last savings and
I decided to spend it on this.

10:56.920 --> 10:58.421
So, you win.

10:59.080 --> 11:03.359
My father has cancer, my children
have to drop out of school,

11:03.360 --> 11:06.639
and I don't have a job.
How could I possibly be winning?

11:06.640 --> 11:09.079
God works in mysterious ways.

11:09.080 --> 11:11.599
This is particularly mysterious.

11:11.600 --> 11:14.023
Oh, one more thing.

11:14.040 --> 11:15.839
I'm gonna be laid up for a while.

11:15.840 --> 11:17.759
I'm gonna need you to watch Kugel.

11:17.760 --> 11:22.504
Oh! There's so much
bad news all at once.

11:25.560 --> 11:26.719
What do we do?

11:26.720 --> 11:31.270
What do you mean, "What do we do?"
We move forward.

11:31.320 --> 11:34.391
It's the only direction God gave us.

11:41.560 --> 11:43.471
Hi, sweetie.

11:46.120 --> 11:47.951
Noah!

11:48.520 --> 11:51.830
I know you're in there.
I can hear you trolling.

11:56.440 --> 11:59.159
Noah, I'm not leaving!

11:59.160 --> 12:00.279
Go away!

12:00.280 --> 12:03.067
Dude, I drove all the way out here.
Open the fucking door.

12:03.640 --> 12:05.159
What's the password?

12:05.160 --> 12:06.239
Um... Is it,

12:06.240 --> 12:09.159
"Your father's dying and
I need to talk to you"?

12:18.000 --> 12:19.639
I knew that was it.

12:19.640 --> 12:22.427
Sunlight, Noah. Noah, sunlight.

12:22.880 --> 12:25.319
Is Dad really dying again or
are you just crying wolf?

12:25.320 --> 12:28.919
It's all over his body, Noah.
The wolf is here.

12:31.840 --> 12:33.719
Kugel, no!

12:33.720 --> 12:35.199
No, no, no, don't stop him.

12:35.200 --> 12:37.159
I can't stand that fucking guy.

12:37.160 --> 12:39.439
Get over here. Kugel!

12:40.960 --> 12:42.541
Lie down.

12:45.360 --> 12:46.941
Your can looks good.

12:48.400 --> 12:50.079
You know when you make
fun of my trailer, Aidan,

12:50.080 --> 12:51.999
you're making fun of
my inheritance from Mom.

12:52.000 --> 12:53.679
She wanted me to live how I choose.

12:53.680 --> 12:55.919
And to be free to pursue
the goals that I have.

12:55.920 --> 12:57.239
And what are those goals?

12:57.240 --> 12:58.559
I thought you were gonna, like,

12:58.560 --> 13:00.199
develop an iPhone app or something.

13:00.200 --> 13:02.359
No, no, fuck apps. Fuck apps.

13:02.360 --> 13:04.759
It's a saturated market.
I'm gonna start blogging.

13:04.760 --> 13:06.599
Look, I have two problems and one,

13:06.600 --> 13:08.039
I think you might be
able to help me with.

13:08.040 --> 13:09.199
- What?
- Kugel.

13:09.200 --> 13:11.479
- Fuck off.
- Dude, I can't raise two kids

13:11.480 --> 13:13.279
and go on auditions and
take care of this dog.

13:13.280 --> 13:15.039
Absolutely not.

13:15.040 --> 13:17.199
Are you kidding me?
This is our father.

13:17.200 --> 13:19.719
Our father. You have
to rally with me.

13:19.720 --> 13:22.599
Oh. Okay. So,
when you get old and sick,

13:22.600 --> 13:25.239
everybody's just supposed to
forget that you were an asshole?

13:25.240 --> 13:26.799
I know he's not easy.

13:26.800 --> 13:29.599
Trust me, no one knows
that better than me.

13:29.600 --> 13:30.879
What's the other one?

13:30.880 --> 13:31.919
What?

13:31.920 --> 13:33.479
You said that there were
two problems, Aidan.

13:33.480 --> 13:35.479
I will help you with the
one that's not that dog.

13:35.480 --> 13:37.119
The other one is that

13:37.120 --> 13:39.719
he's gonna try an
experimental treatment now,

13:39.720 --> 13:42.439
and he can't afford to send the
kids to the yeshiva anymore.

13:42.440 --> 13:45.386
Well, it sounds like you
really got your hands full.

13:45.960 --> 13:47.519
Live long and prosper.

13:47.520 --> 13:49.399
- Are you serious?
- I gotta get back to work.

13:49.400 --> 13:53.063
A blogger never rests.
Don't you dare leave that dog.

14:01.400 --> 14:03.799
...as he searches for his first love.

14:03.800 --> 14:05.586
What a beautiful tortoise.

14:05.640 --> 14:08.319
Can I say something that's
probably gonna piss you off?

14:08.320 --> 14:09.946
I can't wait.

14:10.040 --> 14:11.826
Why don't you homeschool them?

14:13.800 --> 14:16.348
Are you kidding me?
What are we, Amish?

14:16.800 --> 14:20.759
I've been looking online and there's
a whole new movement out there.

14:20.760 --> 14:23.239
Cities that public
schools are suffering,

14:23.240 --> 14:25.902
some parents are
considering other options.

14:26.280 --> 14:28.799
Dad, can we buy drugs
at our public school?

14:28.800 --> 14:29.839
What?

14:29.840 --> 14:32.679
Uncle Noah said he used to buy
drugs at his public school.

14:32.680 --> 14:34.719
No, man, that was the '90s.

14:34.720 --> 14:37.599
This is LA. There's a weed
pharmacy on every corner.

14:37.600 --> 14:39.119
All you need is 50
bucks and a headache.

14:39.120 --> 14:41.199
- Honey, don't tell him that.
- If you're implying

14:41.200 --> 14:42.919
you want me to give up acting,
you should just say it.

14:42.920 --> 14:44.399
I think you should give up acting.

14:44.400 --> 14:45.839
I will not give up acting.

14:45.840 --> 14:47.319
We can't afford private school,

14:47.320 --> 14:48.679
you're afraid of public school.

14:48.680 --> 14:50.119
It's the middle of the school year.

14:50.120 --> 14:53.599
You want to just drop these two
little indoctrinated matzo balls

14:53.600 --> 14:55.799
into a school that's ranked
last in the district?

14:55.800 --> 14:58.985
I agree with you,
but what's your plan, Dad?

14:59.160 --> 15:01.599
Grace, what's the Hebrew
word for charity again?

15:01.600 --> 15:04.467
Tzedakah.

15:06.880 --> 15:08.825
Tzedakah.

15:29.000 --> 15:32.549
Mr. Bloom, Baruch Hashem.

15:33.040 --> 15:35.030
Please have a seat.

15:39.600 --> 15:42.102
Do you ever watch these YouTubes?

15:42.960 --> 15:45.542
YouTube? Yes, I've seen YouTube.

15:46.200 --> 15:51.547
This kitten will not allow his
brother to sleep, no matter what.

15:52.000 --> 15:55.231
You know kittens,
they're always doing something.

15:55.520 --> 16:00.199
Mr. Bloom, please,
can I help you today?

16:00.200 --> 16:01.919
Well, Rabbi, as I'm sure you know,

16:01.920 --> 16:06.519
my father has been paying
our tuition here at Hillel.

16:06.520 --> 16:09.879
Unfortunately, he's taken ill

16:09.880 --> 16:12.679
and he can no longer afford
to cover us anymore.

16:12.680 --> 16:16.627
Oh, yes, I've been
counseling your father.

16:16.840 --> 16:19.559
I am deeply sorry about his illness.

16:19.560 --> 16:21.079
Thank you.

16:21.080 --> 16:24.639
I hope you're not withdrawing
the children from this school.

16:24.640 --> 16:26.039
That's the thing.

16:26.040 --> 16:29.559
We could only afford to
go here with his help.

16:31.400 --> 16:35.063
Ah, yes. You're the actor.

16:35.640 --> 16:37.399
- Yes.
- Uh-huh.

16:37.400 --> 16:41.586
And your wife provides for the family

16:41.760 --> 16:44.199
while you act.

16:44.200 --> 16:45.781
Yes.

16:47.200 --> 16:50.239
But I was hoping that
you might consider

16:50.240 --> 16:52.230
giving us a little

16:54.280 --> 16:55.519
